# Component Rules

## Images

- Always use Next.js `<Image>` from `next/image`.
- Always pass explicit `width` and `height` from the DB row — eliminates CLS.
- Never use `<img>` for content images. (`<img>` is OK for tiny icons.)

```tsx
// GOOD
<Image
  src={img.imageUrl}
  alt={img.prompt.slice(0, 80)}
  width={img.width}
  height={img.height}
  sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, (max-width: 1024px) 50vw, 33vw"
/>
```

## Touch + hover

- Hover-driven UX must have a tap-driven equivalent. Touch devices have no hover.
- Cosmetic effects like tilt/parallax are gated to `@media (pointer: fine)` to avoid mobile jank.

```tsx
// ImageCard: hover OR tap flips. Both code paths must work.
<div
  className="card"
  onMouseEnter={handleHoverFlip}
  onClick={handleTapFlip}
/>
```

## Server vs client

- Default to Server Components. Add `"use client"` only when you need state, effects, or browser APIs.
- Never fetch from Supabase in a client component. Pass data down from a Server Component, or call a service from a server action.

## Loading & error states

- Every list view ships with a `Skeleton*.tsx` placeholder.
- Errors surface through an error boundary — never silent.
